cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.AR 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on providing reliable and high data rate communication services for high-speed trains, which is a networking problem. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes an energy-efficient power-control scheme for mmWave communication, which involves optimizing the transmission power and data rate, and can be related to information theory. 
3. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the use of mmWave communication for high-speed trains, which can be considered as a multimedia application. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a position-prediction model and a power minimization algorithm for efficient power control, which can be related to systems and control. 
5. cs.AR (Hardware Architecture) - The paper uses a realistic direction antenna model and receive power model, which can be related to hardware architecture.
